Title : Land Compensation Act 1961
Text : '''Land Compensation Act 1961''' ([http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/Eliz2/9-10/33/contents c 33]) is an [[Act of Parliament]] of the [[United Kingdom]], which concerns [[English land law]] and [[Compulsory purchase in England and Wales|compulsory purchase]].

==Contents==
Section 5 generally requires that the owner of an interest in land (e.g. a freehold, leasehold or easement as in ''[[Re Ellenborough Park]]''<ref>[1955] [http://www.bailii.org/ew/cases/EWCA/Civ/1955/4.html EWCA Civ 4], [1956] Ch 131</ref>) receives payment for the "value of the land... if sold on an open market by a willing seller".

